  <span id="freeText13517367570494476014" style="display:none"><b>January 1864</b> –General Robert E. Lee faces defeat. The Army of Northern Virginia is ragged and ill-equpped. Gettysburg has broken the back of the Confederacy and decimated its manpower.<p>Then, Andries Rhoodie, a strange man with an unplaceable accent, approaches Lee with an extraordinary offer. Rhoodie demonstrates an amazing rifle: Its rate of fire is incredible, its lethal efficiency breathtaking--and Rhoodie guarantees unlimited quantitites to the Confederates.</p><p>The name of the weapon is the AK-47....</p><p>"It is absolutely unique--without question the most fascinating Civil War novel I have ever read." –Professor James M. McPherson – <i>Pultizer Prize</i> winning <i>Battle Cry of Freedom</i></p></span>
